description:
## Theory
RML allows more types of data sources than just CSV files. To use a different type of data source you need to change the ***rml:referenceFormulation*** object to the proper one. Moreover, a ***rml:iterator*** must be defined.

    <#TriplesMap> rml:logicalSource [ 
		    rml:source "filePath"; 
		    rml:referenceFormulation dataType ;
		    rml:iterator "iteratorForTheDataType"
	    ] ;

In the first examples we used the ***rml:logicalSource*** without specifying any ***rml:iterator***. That is due to RML use the iterator row as default. So this property is not needed in the case of using CSVs or TSVs as data source.

When the data source is in JSON format, the mapping must specify the dataType as ***ql:JSONPath***. In addition, a JSON Path iterator must be provided in order to split the original data and iterate over the fragments. 

## Hands-on
### Task
Complete the mapping below specifying that the format of the file is JSON by using ***ql:JSONPath***, provide as iterator "$.*", and specify that the subjects are ***sch:Place***.
### JSON file content


    [
	    {
		    "name": "Oneonta",
		    "surface": "90.16",
		    "population": "1812",
		    "latitude": "44.9625428",
		    "longitude": "-74.4168577"
		},
		{
		    "name": "Iowa",
		    "surface": "167.2",
		    "population": "133611",
		    "latitude": "29.6862705",
		    "longitude": "-82.319746"
		}, 
		...
	]

user_template:
@prefix rr: <http://www.w3.org/ns/r2rml#> .
@prefix rml: <http://semweb.mmlab.be/ns/rml#> .
@prefix ql: <http://semweb.mmlab.be/ns/ql#> .
@prefix transit: <http://vocab.org/transit/terms/> .
@prefix xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .
@prefix foaf: <http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/> .
@prefix sch: <https://schema.org/> .
@base <http://example.com/ns#> .

<#TriplesMap> rml:logicalSource [
			rml:source "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/helio-ecosystem/helio-ecosystem/main/resources/mappings-data/ldac/plain_locations.json" ;
			rml:referenceFormulation # WRITE HERE ;
			rml:iterator # WRITE HERE
		] ;
		rr:subjectMap [
			rr:template "http://sample.com/resource/{name}" ;
			rr:termType rr:IRI ;
			rr:class # WRITE HERE
		] .

solution_template:
@prefix rr: <http://www.w3.org/ns/r2rml#> .
@prefix rml: <http://semweb.mmlab.be/ns/rml#> .
@prefix ql: <http://semweb.mmlab.be/ns/ql#> .
@prefix transit: <http://vocab.org/transit/terms/> .
@prefix xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .
@prefix foaf: <http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/> .
@prefix sch: <https://schema.org/> .
@base <http://example.com/ns#> .

<#TriplesMap> rml:logicalSource [
			rml:source "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/helio-ecosystem/helio-ecosystem/main/resources/mappings-data/ldac/plain_locations.json" ;
			rml:referenceFormulation ql:JSONPath ;
			rml:iterator "$.*"
		] ;
		rr:subjectMap [
			rr:template "http://sample.com/resource/{name}" ;
			rr:termType rr:IRI ;
			rr:class sch:Place
	] .
